      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just that \"reaching out\" feels like more work, and i don't have any work left in me. it's like i'm running on an empty tank and everyone keeps telling me to just find more fuel, but there isn't any. why is the only solution always \"keep trying\" when trying is what broke me in the first place? it feels so illogical to keep pushing against a wall that's already crushed me.",
